<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Orders Survey of Illegally Imported Cars </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Orders Survey of Illegally Imported Cars </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2005100294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Implementing the Prime Minister's directive, the 
Ministry of Interior instructed police in localities to conduct 
a survey on the number of cars imported illegally into the 
country, including those imported without complying with the set 
procedures. 
  According to a recent survey, 28 provinces and 
municipalities 
have imported 1,512 cars of various types without meeting the 
set procedure requirements, mostly in Song Be, Tay Ninh, Dong 
Nai, Vinh Long, Dong Thap, Binh Thuan, Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City, 
Long An, Lam Dong, and Ninh Thuan Provinces. 
  Quang Ninh and Gia Lai Provinces reported that they did not 
register any new cars. A recent investigation found, however, 
that Quang Ninh Province registered four cars with fake customs 
clearance documents while the Pleiku City police of Gia Lai 
Province coordinated with the Quang Ngai provincial police to 
register 180 cars and motorcycles using fake customs documents. 

</TEXT>

