<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vietsovpetro `Striving' To Increase Oil Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietsovpetro `Striving' To Increase Oil Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2005102994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
0500 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Vietnam Oil and Natural Gas General 
Corporation's Vietsovpetro joint enterprise is striving to 
exploit various new oil wells and develop old ones to increase 
crude oil production. As of 15 May, the enterprise had produced 
more than 2.5 million tonnes of crude oil. It has also 
exploited the acid substances produced at the bottom of oil 
wells and has signed contracts to improve conditions at various 
oil wells to increase the production output by 8,000 tonnes per 
day. While making great efforts to improve conditions at new 
and old oil wells, the enterprise is renovating the oil tanker 
Ba Vi to assist in the exploitation of oil fields in the third 
quarter this year. 

</TEXT>

