BFN 

  [Text] The Office of the National Assembly held a news 
conference today to announce the agenda of the Ninth National 
Assembly's fifth session. 
  Comrade Vu Mao, chairman of the Office of the National 
Assembly, said that the fifth session of the Ninth National 
Assembly will open on 26 May and continue for about one month. 
The main agenda includes debating and passing a code of law and 
five draft laws, examining the situation regarding the 
implementation of the 1994 tasks during the first months of the 
year, and other matters. 
  Also at the news conference, Comrade Vu Mao presented a 
National Assembly Standing Committee resolution promulgating 
coordination between state authorities in directing and 
organizing the implementation of the National Assembly 
resolution on practicing thrift and fighting wasteful spending, 
corruption, and smuggling. 

</TEXT>

