<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Conferences To Focus on Increasing Imports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Conferences To Focus on Increasing Imports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2305083294 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 May 
94 Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2305083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government will hold a trade conference (to be 
chaired by Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata) on 15 June to discuss 
import-increasing measures at both the government and 
private-sector levels in an effort to reduce Japan's trade 
surplus. It will invite financial representatives from foreign 
countries to Japan for the first time to hear their opinions on 
such issues as deregulation measures in connection with foreign 
firms' access to the Japanese market. The Japanese industrial 
circle will also brief on its efforts to expand imports and will 
make requests to the government. In response, the government 
plans to reflect their opinions and requests in concrete 
measures in an outline of reforming external economic relations 
to be worked out at the end of June. 
  The government has decided to invite foreign representatives 
to Japan because it has concluded that it is necessary to hear 
opinions directly from foreign businessmen in order to increase 
imports. 

</TEXT>

