<H3> <TI>   18, 19 May U.S., ROK Military Exercises Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    18, 19 May U.S., ROK Military Exercises Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105061394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0544 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2105061394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 21 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists on 
May 18 and 19 mobilized fighters of the marines from overseas 
bases to stage an air war exercise in coordination with the 
flying corps of the U.S. Air Force in South Korea, according to 
military sources. 
  Participating in the exercise were formations of Japan-based 
pursuit-assault planes and F-16 and F-15 fighter-bombers, A-10 
assault planes and OA-10 observation planes of the U.S. Air 
Force stationed in South Korea. 
  Meanwhile, on the 19th the South Korean puppets deployed 
armed forces and large-calibre artillery groups in Inje, Paju 
and Yonchon counties adjacent to the demilitarized zone of the 
military demarcation line, and dropped commandos by formations 
of transport planes and helicopters. And they fired hundreds of 
shells and large-calibre machinegun bullets. 

</TEXT>

