<H3> <TI>   1,500 Students Reportedly Hold Rally in Seoul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1,500 Students Reportedly Hold Rally in Seoul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105131394 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1157 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2105131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1157 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This is the just-in news. According to broadcast 
reports from Seoul, some 1,500 students belonging to the South 
Korean Federation of General Student Councils convened at Seoul 
Municipal University on 21 May and held a rally for the 
resolution of inheriting the spirit of the 18 May Kwangju 
popular resistance and opposing the United States. 
  In the meeting, the students called on the United States to 
withdraw its nuclear inspection suppression on the North. 
Denouncing the United States for imposing unreasonable pressure 
on the North for its own interests, the participants strongly 
called for the pullout of the nuclear weapons of the U.S. troops 
occupying South Korea and the suspension of the commotions of 
nuclear inspection suppression against the North. 
  After the rally, the students, in a high spirit, staged a 
street demonstration and marched toward Chongno Street in 
groups. As the students finally advanced into Chongno Street at 
around 1730, the police ran amok to stop them. However, the 
students continued a violent struggle without yielding to them. 
This has been the just-in news. 

</TEXT>

