<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Message Accuses ROK of Abducting DPRK Loggers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Message Accuses ROK of Abducting DPRK Loggers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105053294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0522 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2105053294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 21 (KCNA) -- The secretariat of the 
Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland 
[CPRF] sent an emergency telephone message to the South Korean 
puppet board of unification today denouncing the South Korean 
puppets for kidnapping lumbermen of the North working in the Far 
East of Russia. 
  The message was conveyed through the North-South Liaison 
Office at Panmunjom. 
  Recalling that the North side had warned against the 
kidnapping of North's lumbermen by the South side in the far 
east of Russia, the message said: 
  Your side kidnapped again our six citizens engaged in normal 
tree-felling in the Far East of Russia on May 18 and 20 and took 
them to Seoul. 
  Such a shameless, inhuman and barbaric act committed by your 
side against fellow countrymen even in an alien land is a 
heinous crime destroying harmonious families and increasing the 
number of families living separated on this land and a 
deliberate challenge aimed at extremely deteriorating the 
relations between the North and the South which have alreay 
reached an impasse. This has aroused irrepressible indignation 
among the entire fellow countrymen. 
  Your side's shocking crime can never be covered up with 
anything nor can it be tolerated. 
  Though your side is claiming that our lumbermen defected to 
the South, its maladroit trick is nothing but a drama the 
deceptive nature of which has already been fully revealed. 
  The authorities of your side must unconditionally and 
promptly send all the kidnapped lumbermen back to the North and 
apologize to the nation and the world for the inhuman crimes it 
perpetrated, undermining the dignity of the nation in an alien 
land. 
  If your side refuse to send them back to the North and 
continue kidnapping our lumbermen, it would entail grave 
consequences in the North-South relations as a whole and the 
South side would have to pay dearly for it. 
  Your side will be held wholly responsible for all the 
consequences to be entailed in the North-South relations and 
history and the nation will never tolerate your side's inhuman 
and anti-national crimes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

