<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation of American Committee Departs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation of American Committee Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105114694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1109 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2105114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 21 (KCNA) -- The delegation of the 
American Committee on Korea led by its Executive Director John 
M. Swomley left here today after concluding its 12-day visit to 
Korea. 
  During its stay in Korea, the delegation visited 
Mangyongdae, 
the Tower of the Chuche Idea, the Pyongyang Maternity Hospital, 
the monument to the victorious fatherland liberation war, 
Panmunjom and other places. 
  After visiting Mangyongdae, the head of the delegation said 
he thought a lot, noting that President Kim Il-song who was born 
into a poor family is a people's leader. 
  Witnessing the concrete wall built by the U.S. imperialists 
and the South Korean puppets in the area south of the Military 
Demarcation Line, he stressed that the United States must pull 
its forces and nuclear weapons out of South Korea. 

</TEXT>

