<DOCNO> FBIS4-53654 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas099_c_94022" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-099 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pyongyang Papers Mark National Day of Cameroon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pyongyang Papers Mark National Day of Cameroon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2005130494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1027 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2005130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["National Day of Cameroon" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 20 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang-based papers 
today observe the national day of Cameroon. 
  The Cameroonian people who have registered successes in the 
endeavours to consolidate the national independence in the past 
days are today making energetic efforts to promote the national 
unity and the stability of the country against the interference 
of outside forces and develop the economy, MINJU CHOSON in a 
signed article says, and goes on: 
  Pursuing the non-aligned policy externally, the Cameroonian 
Government is strengthening the friendly and cooperative 
relations with many countries and striving for peace in Africa. 
  Though Korea and Cameroon are far away from each other 
geographically, their peoples have long since forged and 
developed the friendly and cooperative relations. 
  Believing that these relations between Korea and Cameroon 
will further develop in the future, the Korean people wish the 
Cameroonian people greater success in the work for national 
unity and economic development. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

