<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reunification Liaison Committee Issues Bulletin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105061294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0538 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2105061294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 21 (KCNA) -- The International 
Liaison Committee for the Reunification and Peace in Korea 
printed a bulletin on May 10. 
  The bulletin carried articles entitled "Struggle of South 
Korean Democratic Forces Against the U.S. Imperialists' 
Aggression", "Members of the International Environmental 
Organisation 'Greenpeace' Participate in Demonstration Against 
Nuclear Waste Pollution in South Korea" and so on. 
  The bulletin in an article headlined "The Korean Armistice 
Agreement Must Be Replaced by Peace Agreement Without Delay" 
says that the introduction of latest arms equipment into South 
Korea by the United States is a gross violation of the Korean 
armistice agreement. It calls on all the democratic forces and 
peace organisations of the world to join in the movement for 
putting an immediate end to the escalation of the dangerous 
tension on the Korean peninsula and for replacing the Korean 
armistice agreement with a peace agreement. 
  It carried the gist of the April 29 statement of a spokesman 
for the DPRK Foreign Ministry denouncing the hostile moves of 
the Japanese authorities against the General Association of 
Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon). 

</TEXT>

