<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Selected Works, Vol. 10, Published </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Selected Works, Vol. 10, Published </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2005130194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1024 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2005130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 20 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of 
Korea publishing house brought out the volume 10 of "Kim Il-song 
Selected Works", an encyclopedia of the chuche idea which 
carries famous works of the great leader President Kim Il-song 
in chronological order. 
  The volume contains 33 famous works of those published by 
the 
great leader from January 1987 to December 1992. 
  It comprehensively consummates the outstanding ideas, 
theories and policies of the great leader on further 
accelerating the building of socialism and communism and 
successfully achieving the independent and peaceful 
reunification of the country and the cause of global 
independence, under the uplifted revolutionary banner of the 
chuche idea to meet the requirements of the developing reality 
in which the cause of modelling the whole society on the chuche 
idea has been propelled, and the precious achievements and 
experiences gained in the struggle for their realisation. 
  Consummated there are the unique ideas, theories and 
policies 
giving answers to the theoretical and practical questions 
arising in different domains of the revolution and construction 
including the question of effecting a new turn in science, 
education, public health and socialist culture and the question 
of further strengthening and developing the People's Army. 

</TEXT>

