<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Sends Gifts to Maternity Hospital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Chong-il Sends Gifts to Maternity Hospital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105061094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0525 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2105061094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 21 (KCNA) -- The dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il recently bestowed again a benevolent solicitude 
upon the Pyongyang Maternity Hospital. 
  He sent large quantities of baby's clothes of various styles 
for boys and girls, precious pharmaceuticals needed for the 
manufacture of medicines and articles to be used in ensuring 
medical services on a higher level. 
  Always paying deep attention to the work of the Pyongyang 
Maternity Hospital, he had sent more than seven tons of wild 
honey and over ten tons of unshelled pine nuts on three 
occasions this year alone. 
  The hospital completed in March, 1980, is a comprehensive 
medical service base appointed with latest equipment, which was 
built for women and children on the initiative and according to 
a plan of Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  The total floor space of the hospital is over 60,000 square 
metres. 
  The hospital has a total of 1,500 beds, of which 600 beds 
are 
for the obstetrical section, 400 for the gynaecological section 
and 500 for just-born babies. 

</TEXT>

