<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 21 (KCNA) -- Comrade Kim Chong-il, 
supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, extended thanks 
to medical workers of people's hospitals who had made active 
contributions to the promotion of health of People's Army 
soldiers and set good examples in aiding the People's Army. 
Among them were medical workers of the clinical section No. 2 
of the Neurological Hospital of the Korean General Red Cross 
Hospital, the Sunchon City People's Hospital and the Sariwon 
Railway Administration Hospital. 
  They have enjoyed love and respect of soldiers and civilians 
by showing all sincerity in medical services to the population 
and in medical treatment of soldiers. 
  Comrade Kim Chong-il also extended thanks to the officials 
and employees of the Tongdaewon garment factory in Pyongyang. 
  Over the past 20 years the officials and employees of this 
factory have overfulfilled the factory's annual assignments of 
the national economy on all indices and done a lot of good job 
for the society and the people. 

</TEXT>

