<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KPA Soldiers Commended for Preserving Site </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KPA Soldiers Commended for Preserving Site </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105150094 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2100 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2105150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2100 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army [KPA] 
Comrade Kim Chong-il, the dear leader of our party and people, 
has sent thanks of the Party Central Military Committee and the 
supreme commander to the officers and men of the KPA unit to 
which Comrade Pak Yong-ho belongs for making a contribution to 
building, preserving, and managing the revolutionary site. He 
has also extended thanks to the men of merits in Hoeryong city. 
  Taking the work of building, preserving, and managing the 
revolutionary site associated with the glorious and brilliant 
revolutionary history and the immortal revolutionary feats of 
the party and the leader as their due responsibility as the 
leader's army and the party's army, the officers and men of the 
KPA unit to which Comrade Pak Yong-ho belongs participated in 
this work as a group. They have intensified the indoctrination 
work on the revolutionary tradition through their visit to the 
site. In addition, using their leisure time between trainings, 
they made a great contribution to preserving the revolutionary 
site to its original state handing it down for ages to come. 
  Taking the pride and dignity in living in a place with a 
historic background, some 80 men of merits, including Yu 
Tae-kyu, in Hoeryong city resolved to take part in managing the 
revolutionary site in the city in February 1991. Since then, 
they have carried out the management befitting masters. The 
have not only transplanted some 800 rare trees and flowers and 
set up new audio system around the site, but also prepared 
numerous materials and equipment necessary for the construction 
of the site and took part in the work of introducing the 
revolutionary site. 
  Meetings to deliver KPA Supreme Commander Comrade Kim 
Chong-il's thanks were held at relevant sectors. Functionaries 
concerned, the soldiers of the People's Army, and the men of 
merits were present in the meetings. 
  In the meetings, the comrade supreme commander's thanks were 
delivered amid the participants' fervent applause. Discussions 
for resolution were held at the meetings. 
  A letter of pledge and a resolution to KPA Supreme Commander 
Comrade Kim Chong-il were adopted in the meetings. 

</TEXT>

