<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on U.S.-Japan Framework Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on U.S.-Japan Framework Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Third Day of Talks Called Off </H4>

<F P=102> OW2105151094 Tokyo KYODO in English 1457 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2105151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington, May 21 KYODO -- Japanese and U.S. 
officials on Saturday [21 May] called off a third day of talks 
aimed at striking an elusive deal on jump-starting stalled trade 
talks on ways to increase foreign access to key Japanese 
markets, informed sources said. 
  The two countries were earlier scheduled to resume the talks 
on Saturday. 
  Senior U.S. and Japanese officials huddled for more than 10 
hours in two days Thursday and Friday to "explore" a common 
basis to break a three-month deadlock in the so-called 
"framework" talks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

