  [Text] Tokyo, May 20 KYODO -- Japan will hand over medical 
goods and equipment worth 34,000 dollars to Belarus as emergency 
humanitarian assistance to help the victims of the 1986 
Chernobyl accident, the Foreign Ministry said Friday [20 May]. 
The aid consists of about 3 tons of medical goods and equipment 
that can meet emergency medical demands of 30,000 people over a 
