  [Text] Tokyo, May 22 KYODO -- A Honduras-flagged freighter 
with some 60 non-Japanese Asians on board is approaching 
southern Japan, TBS TV reported Sunday [22 May]. 
  Five patrol boats are keeping watch on the 500-ton vessel, 
identified as the Montana, which was spotted in waters some 35 
kilometers off Tanegashima Island, Kagoshima Prefecture, Tokyo 
