<H3> <TI>   Rice Imports Produce 53 Billion Yen Profit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rice Imports Produce 53 Billion Yen Profit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2005130694 Tokyo KYODO in English 1241 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2005130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 20 KYODO -- The Food Agency said Friday 
[20 May] it made a profit of 53 billion yen in the five-month 
period ended March 31 through emergency imports of rice to deal 
with the poor rice crop last year. The agency said 48 billion 
yen or 90 percent of the profit, which excludes transport and 
other expenses, was transferred to a special account to cover a 
decrease in income by farming households. The agency said it 
made total rice imports of 410,000 tons in the period at an 
average price of 68,000 yen per ton and sold the rice at 218,000 
yen per ton. The agency expects to make a total profit of 300 
billion yen from rice imports in the current grain year ending 
Oct. 30, when it plans to import 2.08 to 2.48 million tons of 
rice, officials said. 

</TEXT>

