<H3> <TI>   DLP Official To Ask PRC To Mediate Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DLP Official To Ask PRC To Mediate Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105080594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0750 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2105080594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 21 (YONHAP) -- The secretary-general of 
the ruling Democratic Liberal Party (DLP) Mun Chung-su will 
visit China from May 24-29 at the invitation of the Chinese 
Communist Party. 
  Mun is to meet with senior leaders of the Chinese Communist 
Party, including Vice Chairman of Political Consultative 
Conference Wu Xueqian, head of International Liaison Department 
Li Shuzheng and deputy head of International Liaison Department 
Zhu Shanqing. 
  Mun and the Chinese leaders will discuss expanding 
cooperation between DLP and the Chinese Communist Party. 
  Mun will explain to the Chinese leaders that the peaceful 
solution of the North Korea's nuclear problem is helpful to the 
continual development of ties between Seoul and Beijing and will 
ask for China's active mediation on the matter. 
  Mun is also trying to meet with President Jiang Zemin and 
Premier Li Peng through diplomatic channels and if Mun has a 
chance to meet with Jiang, Mun is likely to deliver President 
Kim Yong-sam's message, informed sources said. 
  Meanwhile, the Executive Chairman of DLP Kim Chong-pil is 
scheduled to visit China in November. 

</TEXT>

