<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Apologizes for Meeting Cancellation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Apologizes for Meeting Cancellation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2105035194 Seoul YONHAP in English 0323 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2105035194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 21 (YONHAP) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin sent a message to President Kim Yong-sam on Saturday to 
express his regret over the indefinite postponement of the first 
Korea-Russia joint economic committee meeting. 
  The meeting was put off after Russia abruptly cancelled the 
visit to Seoul by Deputy Prime Minister Aleksandr Shokhin who 
was to represent Russia at the meeting slated for May 20-21. 
  In the message, Yeltsin said he was very sorry for the 
cancellation of Shokhin's visit to Seoul due to Russia's 
domestic situation. 
  Russian Ambssador to Korea Georgiy Kunadze called on Vice 
Foreign Minister Hong Sun-yong to hand him the message for 
delivery to President Kim. 
  Asking for President Kim's understanding of the "unexpected 
sitaution" that kept the Russian delegation from visiting Seoul, 
Yeltsin said he was suggesting that the meeting be held in 
Moscow at an appropriate time before President Kim's planned 
visit to Moscow. 
  The Russian president also said in the message his country 
was looking forward to President Kim's visit to Moscow, which he 
said would be very useful to bilateral relations in many aspects. 

</TEXT>

