<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denies Report on Russian Subs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Denies Report on Russian Subs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2305121294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1132 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2305121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 23 (YONHAP) -- The Foreign Ministry on 
Monday denied as "not factual" the recent claim by a British 
military expert that the discarded submarines bought by North 
Korea may be used for military purposes. 
  An article written by a British international naval forces 
expert and that appeared in the recently published "Jane's 
Warships, '94- '95," alleged that North Korea has purchased 40 
submarines from Russia and that there is the danger of the 
submarines being used for military purposes in North Korea. 
  "We have asked Russia about the claim through our consulate 
general in Vladivostok and Russian authorities said there is no 
such danger at all," a ministry official said. 
  Russia, he said, explained they had sold 12 discarded 
submarines, instead of 40 as claimed by Jane's, to North Korea, 
and only one of them has actually been delivered to Pyongyang. 
  Even this one submarine has no way but to be used as scrap 
because the Russian military had removed from the submarine all 
those parts that could be used militarily, the official said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

