<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA May 20 -- President Le Duc Anh received 
here this afternoon Foreign Minister of Republic of Korea (ROK) 
Han Sung-chu now on an official visit to Vietnam. 
  Foreign Minister Han conveyed to President Le Duc Anh best 
regards from President of ROK Kim Yong-sam. Mr. Han said he was 
glad to have seen the achievements the Vietnamese people 
recorded in their renovation process as well as the fine 
development of the economic cooperation between the two 
countries. He stressed that the ROK was ready to share 
experience with Vietnam and cooperate with it in national 
construction for mutual benefit, and for peace, stability, and 
development in the region. 
  For his part, President Le Duc Anh hailed Foreign Minister 
Han's visit as manifestation of the enhancement of the friendly 
and cooperative ties between Vietnam and ROK. He said he was 
confident that with good-will from both sides cooperation in 
economy, trade, education, science and technology, and the 
implementation of projects on infrastructural construction and 
technology transfer would gain good results, thus making 
contributions to the consolidation of peace, stability, and 
development in the region. 
  On this occasion, President Le Duc Anh asked Foreign 
Minister 
Han to convey his invitation to President Kim Yong-sam visit to 
Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

