<F P=102>   BK2005154794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Malaysia cannot accept the statement by Britain 
which wants the Bosnian Government to accept defeat in its war 
against the Serbs. Foreign Minister Datuk Abdullah Ahmad Badawi 
explained that if the statement is accepted, it will mean that 
Malaysia and the whole world agree with the policy of ethnic 
cleansing in Bosnia-Herzegovina. According to the minister, the 
statement made by Britain indicates that the country will not do 
anything to bring about peace in Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

