<H3> <TI>   King Appoints Ambassador, Promotes Army Officer </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Appoints Ambassador, Promotes Army Officer </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2005095494 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0405 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2005095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 20 May (AKP) -- Two personages of the 
former State of Cambodia regime have been nominated by decrees 
signed by His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk, king of Cambodia. 
  Mr. Sek Settha, deputy foreign minister of the old regime, 
has been nominated ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary 
of the Kingdom of Cambodia to the Russian Federation. Mr. Nhim 
Vanda has been promoted to four-star general of the Khmer Royal 
Army [KRA]. He is authorized by the two prime ministers to be in 
charge of the special commission to provide supplies to military 
forces on the front. 
  Under the State of Cambodia, Mr. Nhim Vanda was trade 
minister and deputy defense minister in charge of the Army's 
General Logistics Department. 

</TEXT>

