<H3> <TI>   Alatas Welcomes Ramos Decision on Timor Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alatas Welcomes Ramos Decision on Timor Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2005134494 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia has welcomed the Philippine Government's 
decision to deny entry to all foreign delegates to a seminar on 
East Timor to be held in Manila. Commenting on the decision of 
Philippine President Fidel Ramos on the conference, Foreign 
Minister Ali Alatas said in a press statement in Jakarta today 
that he is awaiting a formal report from the Indonesian Embassy 
in Manila on the matter. He said the conference engineered by 
Ramos Horta [leader of the Revolutionary Front for an 
Independent East Timor or Fretilin] will in fact not be an 
academic seminar on human rights but will clearly be part of 
Ramos Horta's political campaign to discredit the Indonesian 
Government. Accordingly, Alatas hoped the Philippine Government 
will cancel the planned conference as well, because this will 
reflect the common views of the two countries on the matter. 

</TEXT>

