<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khmer Rouge Agree To Attend Peace Talks in Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khmer Rouge Agree To Attend Peace Talks in Pyongyang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2205075594 Phnom Penh AKP in English 0905 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2205075594 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP May 21 -- Khmer Rouge Leader Khieu 
Samphan has agreed to participate in the peace negotiations with 
the Royal Government at King Sihanouk's resident of Chhanghsu-on 
in Pyongyang to be held on May 27. 
  In a message to King Norodom Sihanouk dated on May 19, Khieu 
Samphan said he was very happy to participate in the round-table 
talks for peace and national reconciliation scheduled for May 27 
in Pyongyang under the chairmanship of his majesty king. 
  Khmer Rouge's message was an response to King Sihanouk's 
letter to the faction nominal leader asking for a "clear answer" 
on the proposed round-table to negotiations. 
  The Chhanghsu-on round-table negotiations will be attended 
by 
Chea Sim, president fo the Cambodia People's Party and of 
National Assembly and acting head of state; Co-prime Ministers 
Prince Norodom Ranariddh and Hun Sen; and Khmer Rouge Leader 
Khieu Samphan, King Sihanouk will preside over the talks. 
  King Sihanouk has told the delegations to the talks they 
will 
have to pay for their accommodations and flight tickets. 
  The North Korean Government would pay for the costs of 
hosting the talks in Pyongyang, Sihanouk said. 

</TEXT>

