<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Issues Commentary on Fuel Rod Replacement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Issues Commentary on Fuel Rod Replacement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2005043294 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0400 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2005043294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, in a commentary in the name of Chang Ki-ho, 
a spokesman for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the government 
expressed regret and worry over the fact that it has been 
confirmed that North Korea has begun replacing fuels at the 5-mw 
atomic reactor. 
  The government also urged North Korea to fulfill its duty of 
implementing safety measures in connection with the replacement 
of fuels at the 5-megawatt atomic reactor through immediate 
negotiations with the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] 
which says that there remains the possibility of the 
implementation of safety measures if North Korea no longer 
pushes ahead with replacing fuels. 
  The government also made it clear that it will work out 
further countermeasures through close consultations with 
friendly countries, while watching the results of negotiations 
between the IAEA and North Korea. 

</TEXT>

