<H3> <TI>   U.S. Forces To Conduct `Defense Readiness Drill' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Forces To Conduct `Defense Readiness Drill' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1905072294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0630 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1905072294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 19 (YONHAP) -- The United States Forces 
in Korea (USFK) Thursday [19 May] launched a three-day defense 
readiness drill involving USFK dependents and American civilians 
residing in the country, a spokesman for the Korea-U.S. Combined 
Forces Command (CFC) said. 
  The semi-annual drill called Non-combatant Evacuation 
Operation (NEO) will include the checking of manpower, paperwork 
and the operation to evacuate non-combatants in the event of war 
on the Korean peninsula, the spokesman said. 
  The spokesman added, "the drill is just part of the routine 
semiannual program having nothing to do with the current 
situation in which tension has escalated due to the standoff 
involving Pyongyang's nuclear weapons program." 

</TEXT>

