<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Korean Logger Seeks Asylum in South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North Korean Logger Seeks Asylum in South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2005101194 Seoul YONHAP in English 1003 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2005101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 20 (YONHAP) -- A North Korean logger 
smuggled himself to South Korea on Friday after escaping from a 
North Korea- run logging yard in Siberia, the Agency for 
National Security Planning (NSP) reported. NSP said the man, 
identified only as Chang Il-un, age 30, sought an asylumn in the 
South on arrival at the Inchon harbor aboard a foreign freighter 
which he boarded clandestinely. NSP did not say where he got on 
board the ship. The agency was looking into the background 
leading to his coming to South Korea. 

</TEXT>

