<H3> <TI>   Further on Proceedings at Singapore Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Proceedings at Singapore Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    SRV Planning Minister Speaks </H4>

<F P=102> BK2205122694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2205122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chairman of the Vietnamese State Planning Committee 
Do Quoc Sam said Vietnam needs about $50 billion in the next six 
years in order to develop its economy. This sum is expected 
from foreign aid and loans, with half used in services and 
building infrastructure. Only 12 percent will be allocated for 
agriculture and 38 percent for industrial development. 
  He was addressing a conference in Singapore on trade 
opportunities for China, Vietnam, and ASEAN. 

</TEXT>

