<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by ROK Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Visit by ROK Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Alatas on Nuclear Issue </H4>

<F P=102> BK2305155294 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2305155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Ali Alatas stressed that Indonesia 
is not a mediator in the Korean peninsula's nuclear issue, but 
can only hear the issues from the involved parties through 
diplomatic methods. Speaking at a news conference with his 
South Korean counterpart, Han Sung-chu, Minister Ali Alatas said 
Indonesia, as a neighboring nation and in its capacity as the 
leader of the Nonaligned Movement, can only make an effort to 
hold a dialogue with the International Atomic Energy Agency, 
IAEA, North and South Korea, and other parties such as the 
United States, Japan, and China. Indonesia hopes that through 
such dialogue the Korean peninsula's crisis can be fully settled 
without aggression. 
  Meanwhile, the South Korean foreign minister also hoped that 
the conflict, which has become a concern in the international 
community, can be fully solved. 

</TEXT>

