<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   WPC Urged To Expose ROK's Nuclear Development </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    WPC Urged To Expose ROK's Nuclear Development </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2305154494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1534 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2305154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 23 (KCNA) -- The Korean National 
Peace Committee sent a letter to the World Peace Council on May 
18, which called upon the council to take a serious view of the 
criminal nuclear development by the South Korean authorities and 
lift up the voice informing the world community of it. 
  Noting that the United States invented "nuclear suspicion" 
against the DPRK, describing its 5 megawatt experimental nuclear 
power station as one for the development of nuclear arms, and 
has escalated the anti-DPRK campaign over the "nuclear issue," 
the letter said: 
  The one posing a nuclear threat on the Korean peninsula is 
not the DPRK, a non-nuclear state, but the United States which 
deployed over 1,000 nuclear weapons in South Korea and is hell 
bent on nuclear war exercises directed against the North. What 
is used for nuclear development is not the North's 5-megawatt 
experimental nuclear power station but the heavy water reactor 
and the multipurpose research reactor in South Korea. 
  As South Korean officials in charge of nuclear development 
confessed, the Wolsong heavy water reactor disguised as a 
reactor for "commercial use" and the Taedok multipurpose atomic 
reactor disguised as one for "research", were introduced for the 
purpose of developing nuclear weapons. 
  South Korea is now producing a large quantity of plutonium 
through those reactors. The Wolsong heavy water reactor has 
produced plutonium enough to make 370 or more nuclear bombs 
after it started operation in 1983. Nevertheless, the nuclear 
development in South Korea has not been taken seriously in the 
international community. This is because of the deliberate 
connivance of the United States and the International Atomic 
Energy Agency and their biased act aimed at stifling the DPRK. 
  We consider that the South Korean authorities' nuclear arms 
development can never be tolerated in view of peace in Asia and 
the rest of the world or of the World Peace Council's idea of 
building a nuclear-free world. 
  It is the primary requisite to the denuclearization of the 
Korean peninsula for the South Korean authorities to give up 
their nuclear arms development and dismantle the heavy water 
reactor and the multipurpose research reactor designed for the 
development of nuclear arms. 
  Since the DPRK Government expressed its willingness to 
replace its graphite-moderated experimental power reactor with a 
light-water reactor, they must clearly state to the world public 
their willingness to scrap the heavy water reactor and the 
multipurpose research reactor which are being used in developing 
nuclear weapons. 
  For the Korean peninsula to be turned into a nuclear-free 
zone and a durable peace to be ensured there, it is essential to 
get the U.S. forces and nuclear weapons withdrawn from South 
Korea unconditionally and totally. This is the main question 
which must be solved in removing the danger of a nuclear war on 
the Korean peninsula over which the world is now concerned, and 
guaranteeing peace. 
  We believe that the council will take a serious view of the 
criminal nuclear arms development by the South Korean 
authorities, which is being feverishly promoted behind the scene 
of the U.S. nuclear smear campaign, and lift up voices exposing 
it to the international community. 
  We also express the hope that you will continue to extend 
unstinting support to the Korean people's just cause of peace on 
the Korean peninsula and its peaceful reunification. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-53832 </DOCNO>
