<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Urged To Check ROK Nuclear Arms Development </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Urged To Check ROK Nuclear Arms Development </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2205085794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0819 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2205085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 22 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of 
the South Korean National Democratic Front [SKNDF] (Hanminjon) 
strongly urged the U.S. President to abandon the U.S. commitment 
to providing its nuclear umbrella for South Korea and, at the 
same time, to take measures to withdraw more than 1,000 pieces 
of nuclear weapons from South Korea without delay and promptly 
check the criminal nuclear arms development of the South Korean 
authorities, the Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation 
reported. 
  In a protest message to the U.S. President May 17 it charged 
that the "White House" has been conniving at the nuclear arms 
development in South Korea which has been stepped up under the 
U.S. nuclear umbrella. 
  The message noted that spent nuclear fuel can be replaced 
any 
moment for the pressurized heavy water reactor (PHWR) in Wolsong 
and the multi-purpose research reactor at the Taedok complex in 
South Korea while they are operating, that the 678,700 kilowatt 
PHWR in Wolsong has yielded spent nuclear fuel including 
plutonium enough to make more than 370 nuclear warheads up until 
now and that the 30,000 kilowatt multi-purpose research reactor 
in Taedok is one for nuclear development which is producing 
plutonium more quickly than the PHWR. 
  While taking issue with the North over its 5 megawatt 
experimental development reactor, the United States has not 
called into question the Wolsong PHWR and Taedok multi-purpose 
research reactor which put out plutonium several ten times 
greater than that, the message said. 
  Calling attention to the fact that South Korea and Japan 
have 
maintained close relations of technical cooperation for their 
own nuclear armament under the U.S. nuclear umbrella, it 
stressed: Far from checking this dangerous conspiracy and tieup, 
the United States put up South Korea and Japan as shock brigades 
in the nuclear racket against the North, thus creating a grave 
nuclear threat not only on the Korean peninsula but in the rest 
of Asia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

