<F P=103> SK2305053594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 23 (KCNA) -- More than 3,000 
villagers of Yangsan, South Kyongsang Province, held the sixth 
rally on May 20 against the construction of a nuclear waste dump 
by the puppet authorities, according to a radio report from 
Seoul. 
  At the rally the promotion committee of the struggle against 
the construction of the Yangsan nuclear waste dump declared that 
the boycott of schools by students in Yangsan and Ulsan would be 
expanded, if the puppet authorities refused to give up the 
project. 
  The villagers demanded that the puppet authorities release 
those taken into custody while participating in the struggle 
against the project and stop police search for those on the want 
list. 

