<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Undisguised Perfidy" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 22 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
denounces the South Korean puppet prosecution for recently 
blocking the people from bringing a suit against the culprits of 
the Kwangju massacre. 
  The news analyst says: 
  When the members of the National Federation for Democracy 
and 
Reunification showed a sign of bringing a suit demanding the 
punishment of 35 culprits of the Kwangju bloodbath including the 
chief culprits -- traitors Chon Tu-hwan and No Tae-u -- the 
puppet Seoul District prosecution authorities hurriedly 
mobilized riot police for a strict cordon around the prosecution 
building and violently blocked dissidents from entering the gate. 
  This is a truculent anti-democratic act of fascist tyrants 
ruthlessly trampling down the elementary democratic rights of 
the people. 
  It is a very legitimate exercise of their right for the 
people to indict the culprits of the Kwangju massacre and demand 
their punishment. 
  Moreover, there is no ground for the present 
"civilian"-veiled "government" of South Korea, which pretends to 
have inherited the "spirit of the Kwangju resistance," to refuse 
to meet the people's demand. The violent hindrance of the 
presentation of the indictment was aimed at burying into 
obscurity the crimes of the murderers of Kwangju people and 
defend them. 
  The Kim Yong-sam clique, though "civilian"-veiled, is a 
fascist group little different from the military dictatorial 
forces of the "Fifth and Sixth Republics." 
  If the clique thinks it can go scotfree, protecting the 
culprits of the Kwangju massacre, it is foolish and stupid, 
indeed. 
  The South Korean people's unanimous will is to clarify the 
truth behind the Kwangju bloodbath and judge and punish the 
murderers. 
  If the Kim Yong-sam group, turning a deaf ear to their 
demand, persists in "defending" the murderers of Kwangju, it 
will encounter greater protest and criticism from the people. 

</TEXT>

