  [Text] Pyongyang, May 23 (KCNA) -- The Kim Yong-sam fascist 
clique have defined the South Korean Federation of General 
Student Councils (Hanchongnyon), the patriotic vanguard of the 
South Korean students, as "an organization benefiting the enemy" 
and threw a police dragnet to arrest its chairman and the 
chairman of its national reunification committee. This is a 
premeditated fascist offensive to lacerate with the bayonet 
Hanchongnyon and students that are taking the lead in the 
movement for independence, democracy and reunification. 
  NODONG SINMUN says this in a commentary today. 
  Noting that Hanchongnyon resolved to build itself up more 
solidly and invigorate the movement for independence, democracy 
and reunification at the second-term inauguration of 
Hanchongnyon, the paper says: This deserves a praise by nation, 
not suppression. 
  The analyst continues: 
  The Kim Yong-sam group's repressive offensive against 
Hanchongnyon is part of its persistent moves to destroy 
Hanchongnyon. 
  The Kim Yong-sam clique of traitors are scheming to block 
the 
action of the pro-reunification democratic forces and ensure the 
security of their power by getting rid of Hanchongnyon, the 
vanguard of the movement for independence against the United 
States, for democracy against fascism and for national 
reunification. 
  Their repressive offensive against Hanchongnyon will add to 
their crimes. 
  The Kim Yong-sam group must promptly stop the fascist 
suppression of Hanchongnyon and students and step down from 
power. 

</TEXT>

