<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports Korean Students Assaulted in Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reports Korean Students Assaulted in Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2205085694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0809 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2205085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 20 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- Some 
17 Japanese middle school students on May 13 committed a group 
assault on four third-year middle class boys of the Tokyo Korean 
Primary and Middle School No. 1 at the plaza of the department 
store in downtown Matsudo, Chiba Prefecture. 
  Due to the assault, one of the Korean schoolboys suffered an 
injury. It will reportedly take ten days for him to recover. 
  Representatives of the Chiba Prefectural headquarters and 
Tokatsu branch of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) and teachers and students of the school on May 
19 called at the Matsudo Police Station to inform it of the 
damage and demanded that it take an appropriate measure to 
prevent the recurrence of such grave case. 
  A series of cases prove that the anti-DPRK, anti-Chongnyon 
campaign of the Japanese authorities is also directed against 
Korean students in Japan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

