<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Protests `Suppression' by Authorities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Protests `Suppression' by Authorities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2305103594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1001 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2305103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 20 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- O 
Hyong-chin, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of 
the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) 
and chairman of its Osaka prefectural headquarters, and other 
delegates of Chongnyon in Kinki District called at the central 
office of the Japan Social-Democratic Party on May 20 as regards 
the unjustifiable suppression of the Osaka prefectural 
organisation of Chongnyon by the Japanese police and handed a 
letter of request addressed to the party to the chairman of the 
Central Executive Committee of the party, Tomiichi Murayama. 
  Chairman Murayama said the search of the Osaka prefectural 
organisation of Chongnyon must not be repeated and his party 
will in the future examine a countermeasure and make active 
efforts for a stop to the suppression of Chongnyon at the Diet 
and at various opportunities. 
  Delegates of Chongnyon in the Kinki District met in Tokyo on 
May 19 and 20 Japanese Dietmen from the district and Koreans 
under the Osaka prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon staged a 
protest against the police on May 16 and 17, strongly demanding 
an immediate stop to the unjust political suppression of 
Chongnyon and an apology for it and an immediate return of the 
things confiscated in the search. 

</TEXT>

