<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Leaders Support Korean `Cause' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Party Leaders Support Korean `Cause' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2305104394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1015 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2305104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 23 (KCNA) -- Foreign party and state 
leaders expressed full support and solidarity for the Korean 
people's cause of national reunification when they recently met 
the DPRK ambassadors to their countries. 
  Secretary General of the Central Committee of the Algerian 
National Liberation Front Abdel Hamid Mehri said his party would 
always stand firmly on the side of the Korean people and 
actively support the Workers' Party and people of Korea in their 
struggle to repulse the imperialists' pressure and interference. 
  Micheslav Ivanovich Griv, chairman of the Supreme Soviet of 
Belarus, said the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula must be 
settled in a peaceful way and by means of negotiations. "This 
is the invariable stand of the Supreme Soviet and Government of 
Belarus," he declared. 
  He supported the Korean people's cause of national 
reunification. 
  Chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and 
Students of Peru Genaro Ledesma Izquieta said no moves of the 
Japanese reactionaries could frighten the Korean people guided 
by the great leader Comrade President Kim Il-song and the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  "We will extend invariable support and solidarity to the 
cause of socialism of the Workers' Party of Korea and the cause 
of reunification of the Korean people," he stressed. 

</TEXT>

