<H3> <TI>   Hanminjon Holds News Conference in Cuba </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hanminjon Holds News Conference in Cuba </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2305053394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0444 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2305053394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Press Conference at Hanminjon Mission in Cuba" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Havana, May 21 [dateline as received] (KCNA) -- A 
press conference was held at the mission of the South Korean 
National Democratic Front (Hanminjon) in Cuba on May 18 on the 
occasion of the 14th anniversary of the Kwangju popular uprising. 
  At the press conference Deputy Chief of the Mission Kim 
Chang-su said that the Kwangju popular uprising was a heroic 
resistance in which more than one million people fought, 
controlling Kwangju city for ten days, and which developed the 
anti-U.S., anti-fascist struggle to a higher stage. 
  "Through the struggle the South Korean people clearly saw 
the 
true color of U.S. imperialism and began to direct the sharp 
edge of their struggle to it," he noted, and said: "U.S. 
imperialism is the very one trying to destroy our nation with a 
nuclear war." 
  "The United States is driving the situation on the Korean 
peninsula to the brink of war by continuously shipping Patriot 
and other war equipment into South Korea and staging `Rimpac' 
exercises. This is a challenge to our nation which loves peace," 
he stated. 
  He said that the traitor Kim Yong-sam is keeping the 
"National Security Law" the abolition of which is demanded even 
by the United States, is expanding the "Security Planning Board" 
and getting frantic in suppression in order to block the road of 
independence, democracy and reunification, and is defending the 
traitors Chon Tu- hwan and No Tae-u, the real criminals in the 
Kwangju massacre, thus making it plain that he is of the same 
clan with the preceding military dictators. 
  "The entire people should unite as one, rise up in the 
second 
Kwangju resistance and build an independent, democratic new 
society free from foreign forces and fascism and accelerate the 
reunification of the country on all accounts," he said. 

</TEXT>

