<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Sends Birthday Table to Centenarian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Chong-il Sends Birthday Table to Centenarian </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2205083294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0801 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2205083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 22 (KCNA) -- The dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il sent a centenary birthday table to Chong 
Chae-myong, an old man residing in Tokchon City, South Pyongan 
Province. 
  The birthday table was conveyed to him on May 21. 
  Born into a poor peasant family in Chongdo County, North 
Kyongsang Province, he barely eked out his livelihood during the 
feudal period and under the Japanese imperialist rule as a farm 
hand, tenant farmer and day labourer. 
  He could enjoy a worthy life and happiness only after the 
liberation of the country. During the fatherland liberation war 
he took an active part in the drive for increased wartime grain 
production and in aiding the front. In the postwar period he 
was the first to join an agricultural cooperative and worked 
hard to reap bumper crops every year. 
  Now, he has a big family of nearly 50. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

