<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Potong River Project Anniversary Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Potong River Project Anniversary Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2205085894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0813 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2205085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 22 (KCNA) -- Working people here 
significantly marked the lapse of 48 years since the great 
leader President Kim Il-song participated in the ground-breaking 
ceremony of the Potong River improvement project and kindled the 
first flame of grand nature-harnessing . 
  On May 21, 1946, President Kim Il-song initiated the Potong 
River improvement project as the first undertaking for carrying 
into practice the plan of land administration he had matured in 
the period of the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, and took 
up the first spade at the ceremony. The project was completed 
in only 55 days thanks to the wise guidance of President Kim 
Il-song and to the great zeal and will of builders and Pyongyang 
citizens to build the country. 
  With a view to conveying down through generations the 
immortal feat of President Kim Il-song, the Workers' Party and 
people of Korea set up a monument to the Potong River 
improvement project on the spot and annually celebrate May 21 as 
"day of builders". 
  A meeting of working people in the capital city took place 
in 
front of the monument on May 21. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

