<H3> <TI>   Defense Issues Council Sets Topics for Review </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Issues Council Sets Topics for Review </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905143294 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 18 May 
94 Evening Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1905143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the morning of 18 May, Prime Minister Tsutomu 
Hata's advisory "Defense Issues Council" (chaired by Asahi 
Breweries Chairman Kotaro Higuchi) held a meeting at the prime 
minister's office. At the meeting, the members agreed to 
propose a review of the 1976 "National Defense Program Outline" 
on three subjects: 1) international situation; 2) comprehensive 
security policies; and 3) tangible measures for defense buildup. 
  On the "international situation," the panel is going to 
discuss military and social trends of the present world, 
focusing on "Japan's increasing responsibilities." Regarding 
the "comprehensive security policies," the panel will advocate 
"comprehensive measures to appropriately cope with `various 
threats'" in consideration of both military and economic trends. 

</TEXT>

