<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Reviews Plan To Buy Italian Planes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Force Reviews Plan To Buy Italian Planes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2305133894 Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST in English 22 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> BK2305133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Air Force is reviewing its plan to buy G-222 
transport aircraft from Italy, previously approved by the 
Cabinet, Air Force Commander Air Chief Marshal M.R. Siriphong 
Thongyai said. 
  ACM M.R. Siriphong said the Air Force had told Supreme 
Commander Air Chief Marshal Woranat Aphichari of its position. 
He said some aspects of the purchase agreement draft needed 
correction. The contract could not be signed until this was 
done as it could cost the country a lot more money. 
  He declined to elaborate apart from saying the issue had not 
been finalised. 
  The Air Force has provided the Supreme Command with a number 
of options in dealing with the problem. 
  Air Force sources said the urgency of the deal appeared to 
have been overtaken by other priorities after a long delay in 
the purchase process. 
  Supreme Commander ACM Woranat declined to comment. He is 
awaiting an official explanation from the Air Force. 

</TEXT>

